oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Waylon Jennings Press Release: Version 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Jennings, Waylon; Offset printing;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white negatives taped to and framed by a masking sheet advertising Waylon Jennings and containing a biography of his life and accomplishments. The press release describes his arrival in Nashville, his deejay career, playing with the Buddy Holly band Crickets, relocation to Phoenix, playing with The Waylors, and his current success. A handwritten note on the masking sheet says, "250." The press release also contains a photograph of Waylon Jennings, and the negatives would have been used to create a corresponding printing plate.
